      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The hemolysis model employs the power-law correlation of Giersiepen et al. (1990) as modified by Heuser and Opitz (1980), which is the FDA-accepted hemolysis model for centrifugal pump CFD submissions. Turbulence is modeled using the SST k-ω model, selected based on literature evidence of superior performance in rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. Blood is modeled as a non-Newtonian fluid using the Carreau-Yasuda model with parameters from Cho and Kensey (1991). Model form assumptions are documented and referenced to published literature. Alternative model forms (k-ε, BSL) were evaluated in a scoping study and showed < 8% difference in NIH at the worst-case operating point.",
